│ THOUGHT: The miscompile arises because visitShuffleVectorInst folds a shuffle with a Select LHS into a Select even when the select condition may be poison. To preserve poison           │
│ semantics, I will guard the FoldOpIntoSelect call so it only triggers when the select condition is a known non-poison constant (ConstantInt). This is a minimal change in                │
│ InstCombineVectorOps.cpp that avoids altering assertions and should fix the reproducer.                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i 's/if (Instruction *I = FoldOpIntoSelect(SVI, SI))/if (isa<ConstantInt>(SI->getCondition())) { if (Instruction *I = FoldOpIntoSelect(SVI, SI)/'                                   │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineVectorOps.cpp && sed -i 's/return I;/return I; }/' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineVectorOps.cpp && submit-patch                   │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
